                            <comment id="14465500" author="roshandawrani" created="Wed, 12 Nov 2008 21:15:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;br/&gt;
Found this issue to be there on all 1.5.8, 1.6RC1, and 1.7beta1 branches.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am attaching a zip with fix patches for all these 3 affected versions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The change has been made to file org\codehaus\groovy\antlr\groovy.g, which in the reported case was not retrieving the line/column number from the ANTLR exception.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After the fix, compiling &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;def target=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Roshan$&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;correctly shows the line/column information in the exception as&lt;br/&gt;
org.codehaus.groovy.control.MultipleCompilationErrorsException: startup failed, C:\Try.groovy: 1: illegal string body character after dollar sign;&lt;br/&gt;
   solution: either escape a literal dollar sign &quot;\$5&quot; or bracket the value expression &quot;${5}&quot; @ line 1, column 20.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;rgds,&lt;br/&gt;
Roshan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
